<section class="section about fade-in" id="about">
  <h2 class="section-title">About</h2>

  <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-text">
      <p>
        <strong>Morpheus Veil</strong> started with a bass, a laptop, and the
        questionable decision to make music at 3 AM because I couldn't sleep.
        What came out was a blend of alternative rock and electronic textures
        that didn't quite fit into any box — and that's the point.
      </p>
      <p>
        The songs talk about the things that keep you up at night. Mental health,
        feeling like you don't belong anywhere, anxiety, abandonment, wondering
        if it's all worth it — and still looking for something worth fighting for.
        All of it from a bedroom in Mexico, with nothing but a laptop, YouTube
        tutorials and too many thoughts.
      </p>
      <p>
        No guitars. Just electric bass through synths, drum machines, and
        whatever sounds right at the moment. Still figuring things out, still
        experimenting, still playing unreleased tracks to an audience of one
        (my cat). But the music is coming.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-photo">
